name: Asari Diffusion
description:
This is a lora meant to create a variety of asari characters. This is a model trained with text encoder on about 30/70 SFW/NSFW art, primarily of realistic nature. The lora is not particularly horny, surprisingly, but do consider the origins when tagging.

Separate anime release is available as well. https://civitai.com/models/20081/asari-diffusion-anime

Tags: "Asari" is the main trigger. This lora is trained to reproduce blue, green and purple skin with quite a few possible variations of color (but see issues, below). Other tags as appropriate for your model, nothing special. Since the model is trained on a variety of nsfw art, nude pictures work with obvious tags. Have not tried anything hardcore, but should work with an appropriate base model.

Tagging clothes description seems to be enough to avoid nudity.

The model has not been trained to recognize any particual Mass Effect characters, but you will sometimes see Liara's face.

Issues: Sadly, skin color tags often bleed into other parts of the shot, I was not able to figure out many ways around it other than to tag carefully or not tag the skin at all and rely on random. It happens less with blue_skin.

modelVersions.name: Asari Diffusion V2
modelVersions.description:
A significant improvement over the last version, most likely the last release.

  1. More consistent faces at a distance

  2. Less human skin issues

  3. Less artifacts and mutations, more successful generations

  4. Does not force realistic style as much

  5. Usable across wider range of checkpoints, just experiment with lora weights

While it works much better with anime models now, I still recommend using the dedicated anime releases for Anything V4 and AOM, as the loras there are more responsive, but this is a good general model.

Style and Models: Works well with the most checkpoints, recommended weights for the ones I tried. All examples are straight txt2img

DeliberateV2 (0.6-0.9)

Realistic Vision (0.6-0.9)

RPG (0.7 - 1)

Dreamshaper (0.5-0.8)

Chilloutmix (0.8-1)

DalcefoeV4 (0.7-0.9)

Dalcefoe oil paint V3 (0.7-0.9)

DalcefoePaintingV4 (0.7-0.9)

AOM (0.8-1.0)

Anything V4 (1.0-1.2)

Anything V3 (1.0-1.2)

ExpmixLinev20 (0.9 - 1.0)

Settings: Works best at low to mid CFG (3-6), I personally prefer to pick lower end of the scale.

modelVersions.name: Asari Diffusion V1
modelVersions.description:
The original release version.

Style and Models: This Lora does not affect style much and can be with most realistic to semi-realistic models. Meant for use with Realistic Vision 1.3 and Deliberate V2. Does ok with some other models too.

Example images are all straight txt2img.

Settings: Works best at low to mid CFG (3-6), I personally prefer to pick lower end of the scale. Weights from 0.8-1 are recommended.
